description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a skilled, experienced Physiotherapist to join the Royal Devon &amp; Exeter Physiotherapy Team working in Healthcare for Older People at the RD&amp;E on a substantive 37.5 hours/week contract.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post-holder is responsible for providing comprehensive assessment and management of patients based within the Healthcare for Older People (HfOP) wards. The post holder will provide specialist assessment and intervention for a complex caseload, and will take a lead in representing physiotherapy in multi-disciplinary activities. This role will include providing knowledge and expertise around the management of dementia and falls across the Trust and assisting in facilitating the timely discharge of patients. The post holder will have excellent communication skills and an understanding of the pathways across the acute and community service whilst being able to manage the acutely unwell patient.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will work closely with the Clinical Lead Physiotherapist and Occupational Therapist in HfOP facilitating resolution of workload and staffing issues. The post holder will also contribute to leading the training and development of less experienced staff, undergraduates and other professionals as required.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will be willing to work flexibly across seven days if required including weekends and bank holidays.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Typical hours&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;08.15-16.30&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vision is to provide safe, high quality seamless services delivered with courtesy and respect. To achieve our vision we expect all our staff to uphold our Trust values. Our Trust values are: &lt;br /&gt; Honesty, Openness &amp; Integrity&lt;br /&gt; Fairness&lt;br /&gt; Inclusion &amp; Collaboration&lt;br /&gt; Respect &amp; Dignity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to staff with ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon.***&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DUE TO THE ANTICIPATED HIGH NUMBER OF APPLICATIONS FOR THIS POST WE RESERVE THE RIGHT TO CLOSE THE VACANCY BEFORE THE CLOSING DATE.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
